     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "JordanWignerTransform[{q1, q2, ...} -> {f1, f2, ...}] returns a list of \
rules {q1 -> op1, q2 -> op2, ...} corresponding to the Jordan-Wigner \
transformation of qubit operators q1, q2, ... onto operators op1, op2, ... in \
terms of fermion operators f1, f2, .... JordanWignerTransform[{f1, f2, ...} \
-> {q1, q2, ...}] returns a list of rules {f1 -> op1, f2 -> op2, ...} \
corresponding to the Jordan-Wigner transformation of fermion operators f1, \
f2, ... onto operators op1, op2, ... in terms of qubit operators q1, q2, .... \
JordanWignerTransform[expr, {q1, q2, ...} -> {f1, f2, ...}] or \
JordanWignerTransform[expr, {q1, q2, ...} -> {f1, f2, ...}] applies the \
Jordan-Wigner transformation rules to expr. JordanWignerTransform[n] returns \
the list of matrices representing the annihilation operators of n fermion \
modes.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
